<title>INDIA: India forex market at standstill on Bombay holiday.</title>
<headline>India forex market at standstill on Bombay holiday.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foreign exchange trading was at a standstill in India on Thursday as banks in Bombay, the country's commercial capital, were closed for a local holiday.</p>
<p>The Indian rupee closed on Wednesday at 35.865/875 per dollar, weakening from Tuesday's close at 35.830/835 as central bank dollar purchases continued, dealers said.</p>
<p>Bombay banks reopen on Friday.</p>
